file\nThe firsr move In this direction Is In\nVevv England where the Boston and\nM-Ine tr.itllc experts are at work on near\nschedule'\nMoney anil pvt Vork\nIn J' at what meatuie the new currency\nstem will succeed In keeping; funds\njiway from ?'ow York, which new seek\nnv-rsfment in thl market. Is yet to be\nshown, o n tn fact remains that new\nthe money market, and St -will be .Inter\nesting to wntch how the movement of\ntanking funds will compare with the sea\nsonal developments under past con\nditions Hut, however much the banking and,\ncurrency lawn may be arbitrarily altered,\nIt Is needless to point out that the\necenomic laws will icmatn the same In\ntheir opcrtllons in the money market\nIn other words, the demand for and sup\nply of money will ftlll be subject to\neconomic conditions which will bo re\nflected outwardly by the rates for mom-y\nover extendfd periods. Only for the tlmo\nwill the new Influences make their\npresence felt.\nIf It be true, as often alleged, that a\nfictitious demand In Xew York caused\nmoney to be sent and held there, the\nnew currency law may brlns this ot.t\nThe new law seeks to give a proper dis\ntribution, but It undoubtedly Is true that\nIf the bona fide inducements are. offered\nIn Xew Yo-k the money will en there\nJust as. It would irore to \"Washington or\nany cthtr center.\nNorthern Central Soars,\nXorlhern Central Railway atook con\ntinued to soar on the Baltimore Stock\nExchange jesterday. The quotation was\nbid up to IIS 1-2 without bringing out\nstock ThU Is 21-2 points higher than\nthe final sale on Saturday and 1-2 point\nhigher than the quotation current on\nWednesday last\nWhile there was again a lack of offi\ncial information relative to the reported\nnegotiations pending for a settlement\nout of court of the litigation which has\nprevented the execution of the lease of\nthe road to the Pennsylvania Railroad,\nthere eems to be no doubt that over\ntures have beer, made and the financial\ndistrict Is confident an 